label.value: antigen processing and presentation initiated by receptor mediated uptake of antigen

value.value: Antigen processing and presentation which is initiated by uptake of antigen bound to a cell surface receptor.

label.value: antigen processing and presentation following pinocytosis

value.value: Antigen processing and presentation which is initiated by uptake of antigen via pinocytosis.

label.value: cell surface pattern recognition receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by a ligand binding to a cell surface pattern recognition receptor (PRR). PRRs bind pathogen-associated molecular pattern (PAMPs), structures conserved among microbial species.

label.value: cytoplasmic pattern recognition receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a ligand from another organism to a cytoplasmic pattern recognition receptor (PRR). PRRs bind pathogen-associated molecular pattern (PAMPs), structures conserved among microbial species.

definition.value: This term should be used for annotation when it is not known which cytoplasmic pattern recognition receptor (PRR) has been activated. If the PRR is known, consider instead the child terms. The RIG-like family is composed of at least RIG-I (retinoic acid inducible gene I; also known as DDX58), melanoma differentiation-associated gene 5 (MDA5; also known as helicard or IFIH1) and LGP2.

label.value: endosomal pattern recognition receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a ligand to an intracellular vesicle pattern recognition receptor (PRR). PRRs bind pathogen-associated molecular pattern (PAMPs), structures conserved among microbial species.

label.value: MyD88-dependent toll-like receptor signaling pathway

value.value: A toll-like receptor signaling pathway in which the MyD88 adaptor molecule mediates transduction of the signal. Toll-like receptors directly bind pattern motifs from a variety of microbial sources to initiate an innate immune response.

label.value: MyD88-independent toll-like receptor signaling pathway

value.value: A toll-like receptor signaling pathway not relying on the MyD88 adaptor molecule. Toll-like receptors directly bind pattern motifs from a variety of microbial sources to initiate innate an immune response.

label.value: immune response-activating signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated by a ligand binding to its receptor that lead to the activation or perpetuation of an immune response.

label.value: innate immune response-activating signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated by a ligand binding to its receptor that lead to the activation or perpetuation of an innate immune response.

label.value: immune response-regulating signaling pathway

value.value: The cascade of processes by which a signal interacts with a receptor, causing a change in the level or activity of a second messenger or other downstream target, and ultimately leading to the activation, perpetuation, or inhibition of an immune response.

label.value: immune response-inhibiting signal transduction

value.value: The cascade of processes by which a signal interacts with a receptor, causing a change in the level or activity of a second messenger or other downstream target, and ultimately leading to inhibition of an immune response.

label.value: innate immune response-inhibiting signal transduction

value.value: The cascade of processes by which a signal interacts with a receptor, causing a change in the level or activity of a second messenger or other downstream target, and ultimately leading to inhibition of an innate immune response.

label.value: immune response-inhibiting cell surface receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor on the surface of the target cell capable of inhibiting an immune response.

label.value: immune response-regulating cell surface receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor on the surface of the target cell capable of activating, perpetuating, or inhibiting an immune response.

label.value: natural killer cell inhibitory signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor on the surface of a natural killer cell capable of inhibiting an immune effector process contributing to an immune response.

label.value: T cell inhibitory signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor on the surface of a T cell capable of inhibiting an immune effector process contributing to an immune response.

label.value: inhibitory killer cell immunoglobulin-like receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a inhibitory killer cell immunoglobulin-like receptor capable of inhibiting an immune effector process contributing to an immune response.
